-------------------------------------------------------------------------
External tools invoked at runtime (NOT bundled or distributed)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

The application shells out to the following system tools via subprocess
invocation. They are NOT linked into, embedded in, or distributed with this
application's binaries or release archives — users install them separately,
and each remains under its own upstream license:

  FFmpeg      - https://ffmpeg.org/            (LGPL/GPL, build-dependent)
                Used for video keyframe extraction and as a fallback image
                decoder (e.g. HEIC/HEIF). Invoked as the `ffmpeg` executable
                on PATH.
  Tesseract   - https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tesseract  (Apache-2.0)
                Optional OCR support. Invoked as the `tesseract` executable
                on PATH.
  libheif     - https://github.com/strukturag/libheif  (LGPL-3.0)
                Optional native HEIC/HEIF decoding path; not required (the
                ffmpeg fallback above covers HEIC without it) and not
                bundled.

Because these are invoked as separate system processes rather than statically
or dynamically linked into sms-archive/sms, their (L)GPL terms govern only
the separately-installed tool itself, not this application.

